## Repro instructions:

* Unpack archive [error_design.tar.gz](https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/files/3366143/error_design.tar.gz)
* yosys -s error_design.ys

## Expected behavior

```Verilog
module error_design(a, b, z0, z1);

    input               a;
    input               b;

    output              z0, z1;

    assign z0 = a;
    assign z0 = b;

    assign z1 = b;

endmodule
```
Expected behavior is output `z1` gets assigned to input `b`. `z0` is essentially undefined.

## Actual behavior

* output `z1` gets the assigned to input `a`.
* input `b` gets assigned to input `a`.

Before `opt_clean`:
![error_design proc](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36720790/60774543-2a002000-a0ca-11e9-9dbf-95b5b2706553.png)

After `opt_clean`:
![error_design opt_clean](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36720790/60774545-33898800-a0ca-11e9-8c2f-5708acf3509f.png)

